":"recebNaZjPvbOqk4r","type":"event","group":"event","label":"Prophecies of Zechariah","slug":"event-246","score":17}],"links":[{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"rec2EEptPS7M8gQC3","label":"part of"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recEtv9ql7Hh4XAW4","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recgkFqZovgbr3pAi","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"reco9Wc4YyNXZq43z","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"rec3gWYVMktOUkAzZ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"reczPjeq0UdahiRrn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recmvSKuAxrUd95O2","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recR67sC02MfTx4al","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recA34XfYsCxhyu31","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recxiSg5QZWkj9Hy3","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recNzNKGhPz5qS3Kc","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recdjDOceY7iCq93A","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recUksGHfvwZd6FpB","target":"recebNaZjPvbOqk4r","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recAT97924G2zXCfb","ref":"Zech.9.1","text":"The burden of the word of the LORD in the land of Hadrach, and Damascus shall be the rest thereof: when the eyes of man, as of all the tribes of Israel, shall be toward the LORD.","year":-487},{"id":"recWBsdAu1ZNZhVko","ref":"Zech.9.2","text":"And Hamath also shall border thereby; Tyrus, and Zidon, though it be very wise.","year":-487},{"id":"recZYjJnoLVz8q2O8","ref":"Zech.9.3","text":"And Tyrus did build herself a strong hold, and heaped up silver as the dust, and fine gold as the mire of the streets.","year":-487},{"id":"recIqnCgcLUwDzcXs","ref":"Zech.9.4","text":"Behold, the Lord will cast her out, and he will smite her power in the sea; and she shall be devoured with fire.","year":-487},{"id":"recyNU0wIdIrVd9gE","ref":"Zech.9.5","text":"Ashkelon shall see it, and fear; Gaza also shall see it, and be very sorrowful, and Ekron; for her expectation shall be ashamed; and the king shall perish from Gaza, and Ashkelon shall not be inhabited.","year":-487},{"id":"recsSKNua6sbXCjTV","ref":"Zech.9.6","text":"And a bastard shall dwell in Ashdod, and I will cut off the pride of the Philistines.","year":-487},{"id":"recuVH4krGaj72AJg","ref":"Zech.9.7","text":"And I will take away his blood out of his mouth, and his abominations from between his teeth: but he that remaineth, even he, shall be for our God, and he shall be as a governor in Judah, and Ekron as a Jebusite.","year":-487},{"id":"recKkVjSGWT8227w9","ref":"Zech.9.8","text":"And I will encamp about mine house because of the army, because of him that passeth by, and because of him that returneth: and no oppressor shall pass through them any more: for now have I seen with mine eyes.","year":-487}]}
